rg/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A huge final straight from the American who snatches the gold away from the Team GB runner on the line.\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3521, \"end\": 3529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999742885851, \"rank\": 2.3329293533715987e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3566, \"end\": 3573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7839479078760037e-18, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a great silver for the Brit but he's visibly emotional at missing out on what would have been a famous gold.\", \"from\": 3594, \"to\": 3707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Out comes the Brit onto the track - has he got one more big run in him to make history for Team GB?\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3800, \"end\": 3807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7839479078760037e-18, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, it's third time lucky for Team GB in the women's 400m semi-finals as Amber Anning runs a PB to finish second behind Poland's Natalia Kaczmarek but, crucially, book her place in Friday's final.\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 4008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3905, \"end\": 3907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\", \"score\": 0.9939104487081329, \"rank\": 0.006126827805474194, \"text\": \"PB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\"}, {\"begin\": 3